===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[distinguishable]] [[feature]] of a person or thing
# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} the [[integer]] part of a [[logarithm]]
# {{context|nautical|lang=en}} the distinguishing features of a [[navigational]] [[light]] on a [[lighthouse]] etc by which it can be identified (colour, pattern of flashes etc)
# {{context|algebra|field theory|lang=en}} The [[minimum]] number of times that the [[unit]] of a [[field]] must be added unto itself in order to yield that field's [[zero]], or, if that minimum [[natural number]] does not exist, then (the [[integer]]) zero.
#: A field's [[characteristic]], if non-trivial, must be prime, otherwise the field would not be an integral domain, which fields must be. For example, if a field's characteristic were six, then (1+1)+(1+1)+(1+1) = 0; if 1+1 were labeled ''A'' and 1+1+1 were labeled ''B'', then ''A'' + ''A'' + ''A'' = 0, ''A'' (1 + 1 + 1) = 0 by distributivity; ''A'' ''B'' = 0, and the field could not be an integral domain.

